<DOC><DOCNO> AP890204-0021 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-02-04-89 0205EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-Guyana-USFugitive     02-04 0219</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Guyana-US Fugitive,0224</SECOND><HEAD>Fugitive Cult Leader Suffers Second Stroke</HEAD><DATELINE>GEORGETOWN, Guyana (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   David Hill, the U.S. fugitive andjungle cult leader jailed two years ago for manslaughter, hassuffered a serious stroke, his second in three months, doctors said.   Hill, 60, who calls himself Rabbi Edward Washington, wastransferred from prison to Georgetown Hospital earlier this weekafter a stroke caused partial paralysis to his left side. A strokein November paralyzed his right side.   The former leader of the now-defunct House of Israel wasconvicted in Guyana in 1986 and sentenced to 20 years in jail forordering the killing of one of his followers, James Maion.   Hill, whose hospital room Friday was heavily guarded by police,is also suffering from diabetes and a heart condition. Visitors werenot allowed in to see him.   Hill fled to this former British colony on the northeast coast ofSouth America in 1971 after being convicted of extortion and jumpingbail in Cleveland.   By the early 1980s, Hill claimed a following of 10,000 and 47``synagogues.''   His House of Israel, which had no connection with Judaism, becameknown for breaking up political opposition meetings. After the deathin 1985 of socialist President Forbes Burnham, President DesmondHoyte launched an investigation of the cult leading to Hill'sconviction for manslaughter.</TEXT></DOC>